<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Rachel Riley got caught in a sudden downpour as she left the Countdown studios in Manchester after filming on Wednesday. </p>

<p>The presenter, 34, looked every inch the doting mum as she carried her daughter Maven, nine months, in a leopard print sling. </p>

<p>Rachel was joined by her husband Pasha Kovalev, 40, who carried two large suitcases as they left the ITV studios.   </p>

<p>Rachel Riley got caught in a sudden downpour as she left Manchester studios after filming Countdown on Wednesday with husband Pasha Kovalev</p>

<p>Rachel cut a stylish figure in black jeans and a neon pink cardigan. </p>

<p>She opted for comfort on her feet with white trainers and wore her blonde in a sleek straight do. </p>

<p>The television presenter certainly had her hands full as she carried baby Maven in the sling while pushing a pram and small suitcase.  </p>

<p>The presenter, 34, looked every inch the doting mum as she carried her daughter Maven, nine months, in a leopard print sling</p>

<p>The family outing comes as Rachel revealed her hopes for baby daughter Maven, nine months, to be bilingual as husband Pasha Kovalev only talks to her 'solely in Russian'.</p>

<p>The Countdown star appeared Good Morning Britain recently where she sweetly spoke about her family.</p>

<p>Discussing baby daughter Maven, she said: 'She's got teeth, she's biting us, she's all about chat chat chat!  </p>

<p>Chic: Rachel cut a stylish figure in black jeans and a neon pink cardigan</p>

<p>'Pasha is speaking to her solely in Russian and I'm speaking to her in English so we're hoping she'll be bilingual.' </p>

<p>Rachel sweetly added: 'She's so mobile, she's crawling and can walk with one hand now.'  </p>

<p>The maths whizz also shared that she will be teaching her daughter mathematics but joked: 'At the moment, she can bash cups together!'</p>

<p>Rachel also shared details of the regulations on set for Countdown amid the coronavirus pandemic.  </p>

<p>She said: 'We were quite lucky, but we lost our audience which is a shame as they come time and time again, we're like a little family.</p>

<p>'The person who comes and takes the letters from me is in full hazmat gear and has a spatula!' </p>

<p>Rachel, Pasha and Maven have spent lockdown with her Russian mother-in-law Galina, whose month-long visit to the UK was extended amid the pandemic.   </p>

<p>The couple, who became first-time parents to Maven in December and met on Strictly Come Dancing, have enjoyed extended time off at home amid the global COVID-19 pandemic. </p>

<p>Sweet: The couple, who became first-time parents to Maven in December and met on Strictly Come Dancing, have enjoyed extended time off at home amid the pandemic (pictured in June) </p>
